			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-342716">
									

<p>The Feral also includes elements of the wendigo, a dash of zombism, as well as the idea of a feral child. It was very much a stew of ideas. Glad it didn't come across as cliched! I was worried the blantant reference to the Feral's preference for blood while calm would be a little ham-handed.</p>
<p>Good question! I think I'm going to say that, before the current containment procedures were set up, testing with the SCP showed that, while silver-backed mirrors were more effective in inhibiting spectral travel, manifestations of the Wretch as well as the second state of the Child would induce shattering in the mirrors. The current containment procedures suggesting using polished steel (or they will in a second).</p>

